  "The combustion of glucose releases -2803 kJ/mol. If a runner needs 2000 kcal of energy for a marathon, how many moles of glucose (MW = 180 g/mol) must be metabolized? (1 kcal = 4.184 kJ)": "",
  "About 30 moles": "",
  "About 10 moles": "",
  "About 0.71 moles": "",
  "About 3.0 moles": "",
  "2000 kcal x 4.184 = 8368 kJ needed. Moles = 8368/2803 = 2.98, approximately 3.0 moles of glucose.": "",
  "In a coffee-cup calorimeter, 50.0 mL of 2.0 M HCl is mixed with 50.0 mL of 2.0 M NaOH. The temperature rises by 13.7 degrees C. What is the enthalpy of neutralization per mole of water formed?": "",
  "-114.6 kJ/mol": "",
  "-28.7 kJ/mol": "",
  "-57.3 kJ/mol": "",
  "+57.3 kJ/mol": "",
  "q = 100 g x 4.184 x 13.7 = 5732 J. Moles HCl (or NaOH) = 0.050 L x 2.0 = 0.10 mol. Delta H = -5732/0.10 = -57,320 J/mol = -57.3 kJ/mol.": "",
  "A chemist measures the enthalpy of combustion of ethanol as -1367 kJ/mol. If 23.0 g of ethanol (MW = 46.0) is burned, how much heat is released?": "",
